  "contentHtml": "<h1>Linked List Cycle</h1>\n<p>You are given a linked list with a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation>head</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span>. Determine if there is a cycle in the linked list. A cycle occurs when a node points to a previous node.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/linkedListCycle/LinkedListCycle1.png\" alt=\"Image\"></p>\n<h2>How to Solve?</h2>\n<p>We obviously need to have two pointers that indicate where the linked list has a cycle.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If it does not have a cycle, then surely one of the pointers equals <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><annotation>null</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">u</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ll</span></span></span></span>, right?</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Linked List</h3>\n<p>We are using a linked list so let's focus on the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation>head</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span> of the linked list.</p>\n<p>Let's assume we have two pointers that point to the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation>head</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span>, what would be the behavior of the two pointers?</p>\n<p>Well, imagine a tortoise and a hare running in a straight line. The straight line then leads to a running track.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If the hare is faster than the tortoise, will the hare end of meeting the tortoise at some point?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is the intuition behind the tortoise and hare algorithm, this question is literally asking if the hare catches up to the tortoise if they are racing in a race track.</p>\n<p>Let's set <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation>s</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span></span></span></span> as our hare and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation>f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">f</span></span></span></span> as our tortoise.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation>s = head</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>s</mi><mi>.</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation>s = s.next</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span></span></span></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Goes at a speed of 1.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation>f = head</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mi>.</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>.</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation>f = f.next.next</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">f</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span></span></span></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Goes at a speed of 2.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Try creating a linked list with a cycle and see if the hare meets the tortoise if it going twice its pace. Otherwise, I will create a visual below to demonstrate it works.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/linkedListCycle/LinkedListCycle2.png\" alt=\"Image\"></p>\n<h3>Helpful Hints</h3>\n<p>What if there is no cycle?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Then eventually, fast and fast.next will be set to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><annotation>null</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">u</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ll</span></span></span></span> and you should end the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>w</mi><mi>h</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation>while</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">w</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">hi</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span></span></span></span> loop.\n<ul>\n<li>Return <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation>False</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">se</span></span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Return <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation>True</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">T</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">u</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span></span></span></span> if there is a cycle.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Linked List Solution</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs language-python\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\"># Definition for singly-linked list.</span>\r\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\"># class ListNode:</span>\r\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">#     def __init__(self, x):</span>\r\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">#         self.val = x</span>\r\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">#         self.next = None</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title class_\">Solution</span>:\r\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"hljs-title function_\">hasCycle</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\">self, head: <span class=\"hljs-type\">Optional</span>[ListNode]</span>) -> <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">bool</span>:\r\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\"># Set s and f to head</span>\r\n        s, f = head, head\r\n\r\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\"># Attempt to find the cycle</span>\r\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\"># If no cycle exists, then fast points to null</span>\r\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">while</span> f <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">and</span> f.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">next</span>:\r\n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\"># Slow = 1 speed</span>\r\n            s = s.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">next</span>\r\n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\"># Fast = 2 speed</span>\r\n            f = f.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">next</span>.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">next</span>\r\n\r\n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\"># Fast catches up to slow</span>\r\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">if</span> f == s:\r\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\">True</span>\r\n        \r\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\"># There was no cycle</span>\r\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\">False</span>\n</code></pre>",
